Why this template is useful
   Clean separation of startup (main) from application logic (MyApp::run).
   Unit-test friendly - you can test MyApp directly without invoking the actual executable.
   Scalable - easy to add libraries, more source files, or submodules as the project grows.

Directory layout

   myapp/
   ├─ CMakeLists.txt
   ├─ include/
   │  └─ MyApp.hpp
   └─ src/
      ├─ MyApp.cpp
      └─ main.cpp
